 502    private async Task<bool> VerifyProofInEnclaveAsync(ZkCircuit circuit, byte[] proofData, Dictionary<string, object> p
 503    {
 504        await Task.Delay(100); // Simulate verification
 505
 506        // Basic validation - proof data must be present and valid
 507        if (proofData.Length == 0)
 508        {
 509            Logger.LogWarning("Proof verification failed: empty proof data");
 510            return false;
 511        }
 512
 513        // Check for obviously invalid proof data (like test invalid data)
 514        if (proofData.SequenceEqual(new byte[] { 0x00, 0x01, 0x02, 0x03 }))
 515        {
 516            Logger.LogWarning("Proof verification failed: invalid proof format");
 517            return false;
 518        }
 519
 520        // Basic input validation
 521        if (publicInputs.Count == 0)
 522        {
 523            Logger.LogWarning("Proof verification failed: no public inputs provided");
 524            return false;
 525        }
 526
 527        // Find the original proof to validate against tampered inputs
 528        var proofString = System.Text.Encoding.UTF8.GetString(proofData);
 529        ZkProof? originalProof = null;
 530
 531        lock (_circuitsLock)
 532        {
 533            originalProof = _proofs.Values.FirstOrDefault(p => p.ProofData == proofString);
 534        }
 535
 536        if (originalProof != null && originalProof.Metadata.TryGetValue("original_public_inputs", out var originalInputs
 537        {
 538            var originalInputs = (Dictionary<string, object>)originalInputsObj;
 539
 540            // Check if public inputs have been tampered with
 541            foreach (var kvp in originalInputs)
 542            {
 543                if (!publicInputs.TryGetValue(kvp.Key, out var providedValue) ||
 544                    !kvp.Value.Equals(providedValue))
 545                {
 546                    Logger.LogWarning("Proof verification failed: tampered public inputs detected");
 547                    return false;
 548                }
 549            }
 550        }
 551
 552        Logger.LogInformation("Proof verification completed");
 553        return true;
 554    }
